                            <comment id="17422002" author="paulk" created="Wed, 29 Sep 2021 08:09:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The example given fails when compiled with Indy enabled:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;BUG! UNCAUGHT EXCEPTION: cannot make variable arity: C.m()void/invokeVirtual
	at org.codehaus.groovy.vmplugin.v8.Selector$MethodSelector.setHandleForMetaMethod(Selector.java:660)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;So, it is basically treating it the same as varargs.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
